                <head>219. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5520, “U.S. Scientific Satellite Program,”
                    was discussed by the National Security Council at its May 26, 1955, meeting and
                    approved by the President on May 27. The potential for intelligence collection
                    was a major factor in the decision to proceed with satellite development. <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5520 is printed in <ref
                        target="frus1955-57v11#pg_723">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1955–1957, volume XI, pages
                        723</ref>–<ref target="frus1955-57v11#pg_732">732</ref>.</p>
            </div>
